02/12/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Justice Minister Vesna Skare-Ozbolt announced on Thursday (1 December) that possible compensation to Austrian citizens seeking restitution from Croatia could reach 15.5m euros. The cabinet asked the ministry to estimate the costs after sealing a controversial agreement with Vienna to compensate members of the German ethnic community expelled from Croatia after WWII. 
Also Thursday, a court in Pula sentenced former Croatian Tourism Minister Ivan Herak to four and a half years in prison. He was convicted of fraud and abuse of office in relation to a 2000 project to build golf courses in the country. (Novi list - 02/12/05; HINA, HRT - 01/12/05)
